.TH DAAPPARMOR 1 "2025-12-30" "dumbass-tree" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
daapparmor \- dumbass-friendly AppArmor helper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B daapparmor
[\-\-dry-run] [\-v]
.I <command>
[\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
daapparmor wraps common AppArmor tasks with clearer workflows and guardrails.
It shells out to the standard AppArmor utilities like aa-status(8), aa-logprof(8),
aa-genprof(8), aa-enforce(8), and aa-complain(8).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show AppArmor status (aa-status/apparmor_status).
.TP
.B denials
Show recent AppArmor DENIED messages.
.TP
.B allow
Run aa-logprof to interactively add rules for recent denials.
.TP
.B gen \fI/executable\fR
Run aa-genprof to generate a new profile for an executable.
.TP
.B enforce \fItarget...\fR
Set profile(s) to enforce mode.
.TP
.B complain \fItarget...\fR
Set profile(s) to complain mode.
.TP
.B disable \fItarget...\fR
Disable profile(s).
.TP
.B reload
Reload the AppArmor service (systemctl reload apparmor).
.SH SEE ALSO
aa-status(8), aa-logprof(8), aa-genprof(8), aa-enforce(8), aa-complain(8)
